lead_paragraph: Anastasija Sevastova, who quit tennis because of injury in 2013, became the first Latvian woman to reach the U.S. Open quarter-finals since 1994 when she beat Britain's 13th seed Johanna Konta 6-4 7-5 on Sunday.

headline.print_headline: Latvia's Sevastova Beats Konta to Reach U.S. Open Last Eight
